ary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fychan","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ferch Philip Fychan was born about 1335, in Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Philip Fychan Ap PHILIP, was 32 and her mother, Gronwy Person FERCH, was 32. She had at least 1 son with Walter Ap Thomas. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"about 1335–":"umbes 1335–Surnud","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1305":"1305","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","about 1335":"umbes 1335","about 1365":"umbes 1365","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Llangain, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llangain, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1335–":"noin 1335–Kuollut","1335–Female":"1335–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","about 1335":"noin 1335","abou